<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1515] Wake-up Sender upon blocked on fetching leader metadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1515</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the new KafkaProducer will not wake up the sender thread upon forcing metadata fetch, and hence if the sender is polling with a long timeout (e.g. the metadata.age period) this wait will usually timeout and fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
